01:02:09,859 --> 01:02:13,158
<i>Sew!
A needle pulling thread</i>

700
01:02:13,396 --> 01:02:16,593
<i>La!
A note to follow sew</i>

701
01:02:16,999 --> 01:02:19,797
<i>Tea!
A drink with jam and bread</i>

702
01:02:20,069 --> 01:02:23,800
<i>That will bring us back to</i>

703
01:02:24,006 --> 01:02:30,639
<i>So-do-la-fa-mi-do-re</i>

704
01:02:30,880 --> 01:02:35,510
<i>So-do-la-fa-ti</i>

705
01:02:35,685 --> 01:02:37,380
<i>La-so</i>

706
01:02:37,987 --> 01:02:39,079
<i>Fa</i>

707
01:02:39,255 --> 01:02:40,745
<i>Mi-re</i>

708
01:02:40,923 --> 01:02:46,919
<i>Ti-do</i>

709
01:02:47,096 --> 01:02:47,494
<i>So-do!</i>

710
01:03:02,145 --> 01:03:05,239
The mountains are magnificent,
really magnificent.

711
01:03:05,481 --> 01:03:08,143
- I had them put up just for you.
- Oh?

712
01:03:08,417 --> 01:03:10,612
Even if it's to a height
of 10,000 feet...

713
01:03:10,887 --> 01:03:14,379
...Georg always believes in
"rising to the occasion."

714
01:03:14,624 --> 01:03:16,956
Unless the jokes improve,
I'm taking back my invitation.

715
01:03:17,527 --> 01:03:20,121
You didn't invite me.
I invited myself.

716
01:03:20,396 --> 01:03:22,921
- Naturally.
- You needed a chaperone...

717
01:03:23,166 --> 01:03:25,896
...and I needed a place
where the cuisine is superb...

718
01:03:26,135 --> 01:03:28,797
...the wine cellar unexcelled...

719
01:03:29,038 --> 01:03:31,666
...and the price perfect.

720
01:03:32,041 --> 01:03:33,906
Max, you are outrageous.

721
01:03:34,143 --> 01:03:38,136
Not at all.
I'm a very charming sponge.

722
01:03:40,716 --> 01:03:41,910
Listen.

723
01:03:44,220 --> 01:03:46,484
That's the Klopmann Monastery Choir.

724
01:03:49,492 --> 01:03:51,050
They're good.

725
01:03:52,161 --> 01:03:53,788
Very good.

726
01:03:54,564 --> 01:03:57,192
I must explore this area
in the next few days.

727
01:03:57,433 --> 01:04:00,925
Somewhere, a hungry singing group
is waiting for Max Detweiler...

728
01:04:01,170 --> 01:04:05,459
...to pluck it out and make it famous
at the Salzburg Folk Festival.

729
01:04:05,675 --> 01:04:09,008
- They get fame, you get money.
- It's unfair, I admit it.

730
01:04:09,212 --> 01:04:13,569
But someday that'll be changed.
I shall get the fame too.

731
01:04:20,656 --> 01:04:22,817
Good heavens, what's this?

732
01:04:24,227 --> 01:04:26,525
It's nothing.
Just some local urchins.

733
01:04:41,777 --> 01:04:45,702
This really is exciting for me, Georg.
Being here with you.

734
01:04:46,515 --> 01:04:49,075
Trees, lakes,
you've seen them before.

735
01:04:49,352 --> 01:04:51,980
That is not what I mean,
and you know it.

736
01:04:52,221 --> 01:04:56,180
- You mean me? I'm exciting?
- Is that so impossible?

737
01:04:56,425 --> 01:04:59,485
No, just highly improbable.

738
01:04:59,729 --> 01:05:03,859
- There you go, running yourself down.
- Well, I'm a dangerous driver.

739
01:05:07,637 --> 01:05:11,368
You're much less of a riddle
when I see you here, Georg.

740
01:05:11,574 --> 01:05:14,407
- In my natural habitat?
- Yes, exactly.

741
01:05:14,644 --> 01:05:16,805
Are you saying that I'm more
at home...

742
01:05:17,079 --> 01:05:21,072
...among the birds and the flowers
and the wind that moves...

743
01:05:21,317 --> 01:05:23,512
...through the trees
like a restless sea?

744
01:05:23,753 --> 01:05:25,311
How poetic.

745
01:05:25,554 --> 01:05:27,419
Yes, it was rather, wasn't it?

746
01:05:28,557 --> 01:05:33,654
More at home here than in Vienna
in all your glittering salons...

747
01:05:33,896 --> 01:05:38,253
...gossiping gaily with bores I detest,
soaking myself in champagne...

748
01:05:38,534 --> 01:05:42,265
...stumbling about to waltzes
by Strausses I can't even remember?

749
01:05:42,538 --> 01:05:44,631
- Is that what you're saying?
- Yes.

750
01:05:44,907 --> 01:05:47,239
Now whatever gave you that idea?

751
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:54,470
Oh, I do like it here, Georg.
It's so lovely and peaceful.

752
01:05:54,817 --> 01:05:56,773
How can you leave it so often?

753
01:05:57,053 --> 01:05:59,851
Oh, pretending to be madly active,
I suppose.

754
01:06:00,122 --> 01:06:03,319
Activity suggests a life
filled with purpose.

755
01:06:04,126 --> 01:06:06,356
Could it be running away
from memories?

756
01:06:09,598 --> 01:06:13,489
Or perhaps just searching
for a reason to stay.

757
01:06:14,170 --> 01:06:17,662
I hope that's why you've been
coming to Vienna so often.

758
01:06:18,341 --> 01:06:22,664
- Were there other distractions?
- I'd hardly call you a distraction.

759
01:06:22,945 --> 01:06:25,607
Well, what would you call me, Georg?

760
01:06:27,850 --> 01:06:29,147
Lovely...

761
01:06:30,152 --> 01:06:32,712
...charming, witty, graceful,
the perfect hostess...

762
01:06:32,989 --> 01:06:35,822
...and, you're going to hate me
for this...

763
01:06:36,225 --> 01:06:38,318
...in a way, my savior.

764
01:06:38,594 --> 01:06:40,391
Oh, how unromantic.

765
01:06:40,629 --> 01:06:42,961
I'd be an ungrateful wretch
if I didn't say...

766
01:06:43,199 --> 01:06:46,464
...that you brought some meaning back
into my life.

767
01:06:48,304 --> 01:06:51,034
I am amusing, I suppose.

768
01:06:51,240 --> 01:06:56,030
I have the finest couturier in Vienna
and a glittering circle of friends.

769
01:06:56,245 --> 01:06:59,373
- I do give some rather gay parties.
- Oh, yes.

770
01:06:59,648 --> 01:07:01,479
But take all that away...

771
01:07:01,684 --> 01:07:06,041
...and you have just wealthy,
unattached little me...

772
01:07:06,756 --> 01:07:09,179
...searching, just like you.

773
01:07:14,263 --> 01:07:15,992
More strudel, Herr Detweiler?

774
01:07:16,232 --> 01:07:17,756
- How many have I had?
- Two.

775
01:07:18,034 --> 01:07:19,922
Make it an uneven three.

776
01:07:23,239 --> 01:07:26,265
Still eating, Max?
Must be unhappy.

777
01:07:26,509 --> 01:07:30,434
That mixed quartet I've been trying
to steal away from Sol Hurok.

778
01:07:30,713 --> 01:07:33,375
- What happened?
- Sascha Petrie stole them first.

779
01:07:33,582 --> 01:07:34,879
I hate thieves.

780
01:07:35,151 --> 01:07:38,416
Max, you really must try
and learn to love yourself.

781
01:07:38,687 --> 01:07:41,019
I had to call Paris, Rome
and Stockholm.

782
01:07:41,257 --> 01:07:44,852
- On Georg's telephone, of course.
- How else could I afford it?

783
01:07:45,294 --> 01:07:50,425
I like rich people, the way they live
and how I live when I'm with them.

784
01:07:50,733 --> 01:07:52,724
I wonder where the children are.

785
01:07:53,169 --> 01:07:55,694
They must have heard
I was coming and hid.

786
01:07:55,938 --> 01:07:58,429
I was hoping they'd be here
to welcome you.

787
01:07:58,707 --> 01:08:03,201
Max, do step out of character for
a moment and try and be charming.

788
01:08:12,254 --> 01:08:13,619
Well?

789
01:08:14,557 --> 01:08:15,751
Well what?

790
01:08:15,958 --> 01:08:18,882
Have you made up his mind?
Do I hear wedding bells?

791
01:08:19,128 --> 01:08:21,119
- Pealing madly.
- Marvelous.

792
01:08:21,397 --> 01:08:24,093
- Not necessarily for me.
- What kind of talk's that?

793
01:08:24,300 --> 01:08:25,927
None-of-your-business talk.

794
01:08:26,202 --> 01:08:28,693
I'm terribly fond of him,
so don't toy with us.

795
01:08:28,938 --> 01:08:32,499
But I'm a child. I like toys.
So tell me everything.

796
01:08:32,775 --> 01:08:37,906
Come on. Tell me every teensy-weensy,
intimate, disgusting detail.

797
01:08:39,348 --> 01:08:43,478
Well, let's just say I have a feeling
I may be here on approval.

798
01:08:43,752 --> 01:08:46,778
- I approve of that. How can you miss?
- Far too easily.

799
01:08:47,022 --> 01:08:50,253
If I know you, darling,
and I do, you will find a way.

800
01:08:50,493 --> 01:08:53,018
- He's no ordinary man.
- No, he's rich.

801
01:08:53,295 --> 01:08:55,525
His wife's death gave him
a great heartache.

802
01:08:55,764 --> 01:08:58,858
And your husband's death
gave you a great fortune.

803
01:08:59,101 --> 01:09:01,023
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.

804
01:09:01,270 --> 01:09:05,297
You and Georg are like family.
That's why I want to see you married.

805
01:09:05,508 --> 01:09:09,103
We must keep all that lovely money
in the family.

806
01:09:25,361 --> 01:09:28,319
- What are you doing there?
- Oh, Captain von Trapp.

807
01:09:28,564 --> 01:09:30,623
I was just looking for...

808
01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:34,333
I didn't see, I mean,
I didn't know you were--

809
01:09:34,904 --> 01:09:36,633
Heil Hitler!

810
01:09:37,339 --> 01:09:38,829
Who are you?

811
01:09:39,074 --> 01:09:41,338
I have a telegram for Herr Detweiler.

812
01:09:41,544 --> 01:09:44,342
- I am Herr Detweiler.
- Yes, sir.

813
01:09:49,385 --> 01:09:52,047
You've delivered your telegram.
Now get out.

814
01:09:58,794 --> 01:10:02,150
- Georg, he's just a boy.
- Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.

815
01:10:02,364 --> 01:10:05,197
Things will happen.
Make sure they don't happen to you.

816
01:10:05,434 --> 01:10:08,164
Max! Don't you ever say that again.

817
01:10:08,404 --> 01:10:10,599
I have no political convictions.

818
01:10:10,873 --> 01:10:13,728
- Can I help it if other people do?
- You can help it.

819
01:10:14,877 --> 01:10:17,072
You must help it.

820
01:10:27,389 --> 01:10:28,947
Hello?

821
01:10:31,560 --> 01:10:34,393
You're far away. Where are you?

822
01:10:34,697 --> 01:10:38,554
In a world that's disappearing,
I'm afraid.

823
01:10:39,401 --> 01:10:42,928
Is there any way I could bring you
back to the world I'm in?

824
01:11:08,897 --> 01:11:11,422
- Father! Father!
- There's your father!

825
01:11:12,167 --> 01:11:14,863
Oh, captain, you're home!

826
01:11:23,245 --> 01:11:25,907
Come out of that water at once!

827
01:11:34,957 --> 01:11:37,152
Oh, you must be Baroness Schraeder.

828
01:11:42,464 --> 01:11:45,490
I'm soaked to the skin!

829
01:11:57,479 --> 01:11:58,844
Straight line!

830
01:12:13,529 --> 01:12:15,952
This is Baroness Schraeder.

831
01:12:18,534 --> 01:12:20,331
And these...

832
01:12:20,536 --> 01:12:22,197
...are my children.

833
01:12:23,205 --> 01:12:24,729
How do you do?

834
01:12:25,841 --> 01:12:30,540
Go inside, dry off, clean up, change
your clothes and report back here!

835
01:12:35,551 --> 01:12:37,644
Fräulein, you will stay here, please!

836
01:12:39,388 --> 01:12:42,949
I think I'd better go see
what Max is up to.

837
01:12:53,168 --> 01:12:54,965
Now, fräulein...

838
01:12:56,872 --> 01:12:58,897
...I want a truthful answer.

839
01:12:59,341 --> 01:13:00,774
Yes, captain.

840
01:13:01,076 --> 01:13:05,172
Is it possible,
or could I have just imagined it?

841
01:13:06,682 --> 01:13:11,107
Have my children, by any chance,
been climbing trees today?

842
01:13:11,620 --> 01:13:12,780
Yes, captain.

843
01:13:13,889 --> 01:13:15,186
I see.

844
01:13:15,758 --> 01:13:20,252
And where, may I ask,
did they get these...?

845
01:13:20,529 --> 01:13:22,588
- Play clothes.
- Is that what they are?

846
01:13:22,798 --> 01:13:26,222
I made them from the drapes
that used to hang in my bedroom.

847
01:13:27,035 --> 01:13:29,128
- Drapes?
- They have plenty of wear left.

848
01:13:29,371 --> 01:13:31,259
We've been everywhere in them.

849
01:13:31,540 --> 01:13:36,034
Are you telling me that my children
have been roaming about Salzburg...

850
01:13:36,245 --> 01:13:39,578
...dressed up in nothing
but some old drapes?

851
01:13:39,782 --> 01:13:41,443
And having a marvelous time!

852
01:13:41,650 --> 01:13:44,915
- They have uniforms.
- Forgive me, straitjackets.

853
01:13:45,120 --> 01:13:47,918
They can't be children
if they worry about clothes--

854
01:13:48,157 --> 01:13:49,283
They don't complain.

855
01:13:49,558 --> 01:13:52,254
They don't dare.
They love you too much and fear--

856
01:13:52,461 --> 01:13:54,053
Don't discuss my children.

857
01:13:54,263 --> 01:13:56,151
You've got to hear,
you're never home--

858
01:13:56,398 --> 01:13:57,888
I don't want to hear more!

859
01:13:58,100 --> 01:14:00,625
I know you don't, but you've got to!

860
01:14:01,437 --> 01:14:03,598
- Liesl's not a child.
- Not one word--

861
01:14:03,839 --> 01:14:06,728
Soon she'll be a woman
and you won't even know her.

862
01:14:06,975 --> 01:14:10,069
Friedrich wants to be a man
but you're not here to show--

863
01:14:10,312 --> 01:14:11,677
Don't you dare tell me--

864
01:14:11,914 --> 01:14:15,145
Brigitta could tell you about him.
She notices everything.

865
01:14:15,417 --> 01:14:18,545
Kurt acts tough to hide the pain
when you ignore him...

866
01:14:18,754 --> 01:14:20,278
...the way you do all of them.

867
01:14:20,556 --> 01:14:22,945
Louisa, I don't know about yet.

868
01:14:23,192 --> 01:14:26,423
The little ones just want love.
Please, love them all.

869
01:14:26,662 --> 01:14:28,186
I don't care to hear more.

870
01:14:28,464 --> 01:14:32,560
- I am not finished yet, captain!
- Oh, yes, you are, captain!

871
01:14:34,102 --> 01:14:35,160
Fräulein.

872
01:14:37,439 --> 01:14:40,670
You will pack
your things this minute...

873
01:14:40,876 --> 01:14:43,367
...and return to the abbey.

874
01:14:45,981 --> 01:14:47,346
What's that?

875
01:14:49,084 --> 01:14:50,108
It's singing.

876
01:14:50,786 --> 01:14:53,584
Yes, I realize it's singing.
But who is singing?

877
01:14:54,523 --> 01:14:56,115
The children.

878
01:14:58,994 --> 01:15:00,325
The children?

879
01:15:00,863 --> 01:15:03,627
I taught them something to sing
for the baroness.

880
01:15:09,238 --> 01:15:15,302
<i>My heart wants to sing
Every song it hears</i>

881
01:15:15,544 --> 01:15:18,138
<i>Every song that it hears</i>

882
01:15:18,380 --> 01:15:23,841
<i>My heart wants to beat like the wings
Of the birds that rise</i>

883
01:15:24,119 --> 01:15:27,213
<i>From the lake to the trees</i>

884
01:15:27,489 --> 01:15:28,888
<i>To the trees</i>

885
01:15:29,157 --> 01:15:33,890
<i>My heart wants to sigh
Like a chime that flies</i>

886
01:15:34,263 --> 01:15:38,188
<i>From a church on a breeze</i>

887
01:15:39,034 --> 01:15:43,061
<i>To laugh like a brook
When it trips and falls</i>

888
01:15:43,338 --> 01:15:46,262
<i>Over stones on its way</i>

889
01:15:46,542 --> 01:15:47,873
<i>On its way</i>

890
01:15:48,210 --> 01:15:52,169
<i>To sing through the night</i>

891
01:15:52,848 --> 01:15:58,514
<i>Like a lark who is learning to pray</i>

892
01:15:58,754 --> 01:16:02,918
<i>I go to the hills</i>

893
01:16:03,458 --> 01:16:08,452
<i>When my heart is lonely</i>

894
01:16:09,898 --> 01:16:13,459
<i>I know I will hear</i>

895
01:16:13,902 --> 01:16:19,727
<i>What I've heard before</i>

896
01:16:20,542 --> 01:16:24,774
<i>My heart will be blessed</i>

897
01:16:25,047 --> 01:16:31,407
<i>With the sound of music</i>

898
01:16:32,888 --> 01:16:37,712
<i>And I'll sing</i>

899
01:16:38,293 --> 01:16:45,222
<i>Once more</i>

900
01:17:19,601 --> 01:17:21,398
Edelweiss!

901
01:17:25,307 --> 01:17:28,470
You never told me how enchanting
your children are.

902
01:17:37,119 --> 01:17:38,711
Don't go away.

903
01:17:43,792 --> 01:17:45,191
Fräulein.

904
01:17:48,563 --> 01:17:49,757
I...

905
01:17:51,199 --> 01:17:53,997
...behaved badly. I apologize.

906
01:17:55,804 --> 01:17:59,331
I'm far too outspoken.
It's one of my worst faults.

907
01:17:59,775 --> 01:18:01,265
You were right.

908
01:18:03,712 --> 01:18:05,600
I don't know my children.

909
01:18:06,915 --> 01:18:11,011
There's still time, captain.
They want so much to be close to you.

910
01:18:11,319 --> 01:18:15,210
And you brought music back
into the house.

911
01:18:16,525 --> 01:18:18,015
I'd forgotten.

912
01:18:20,729 --> 01:18:22,094
Fräulein.

913
01:18:24,533 --> 01:18:25,830
I want you to stay.

914
01:18:29,838 --> 01:18:32,602
I ask you to stay.

915
01:18:34,443 --> 01:18:37,935
- If I could be of any help.
- You have already.

916
01:18:38,513 --> 01:18:39,537
More than you know.

917
01:18:59,367 --> 01:19:00,732
Marta.

918
01:19:01,403 --> 01:19:02,700
Curtain!

919
01:19:05,340 --> 01:19:07,467
<i>High on a hill was a lonely goatherd</i>

920
01:19:07,642 --> 01:19:10,031
<i>Lay odl lay odl lay hee hoo</i>

921
01:19:10,212 --> 01:19:12,134
<i>Loud was the voice
Of the lonely goatherd</i>

922
01:19:12,347 --> 01:19:14,406
<i>Lay odl lay odl loo</i>

923
01:19:14,916 --> 01:19:16,975
<i>Folks in a town
That was quite remote heard</i>

924
01:19:17,152 --> 01:19:19,541
<i>Lay odl lay odl lay hee hoo</i>

925
01:19:19,721 --> 01:19:21,780
<i>Lusty and clear
From the goatherd's throat heard</i>

926
01:19:21,957 --> 01:19:23,879
<i>Lay odl lay odl loo</i>

927
01:19:24,059 --> 01:19:29,053
<i>Ho ho lady odlee ho
Ho ho lady odl lay</i>

928
01:19:29,231 --> 01:19:33,395
<i>Ho ho lady odl lee ho
Lady odl lee ho lay</i>

929
01:19:34,569 --> 01:19:37,424
Marta. Marta!

930
01:19:39,808 --> 01:19:41,799
Gretl, the prince!

931
01:19:43,578 --> 01:19:45,808
<i>A prince on the bridge
Of a castle moat heard</i>

932
01:19:45,981 --> 01:19:48,279
<i>Lay odl lay odl lay hee hoo</i>

933
01:19:48,450 --> 01:19:50,645
<i>Men on a road
With a load to tote heard</i>

934
01:19:50,819 --> 01:19:52,775
<i>Lay odl lay odl loo</i>

935
01:19:53,321 --> 01:19:55,346
<i>Men in the midst
Of a table d'hôte heard</i>

