I'd be happy to help you.

985
01:22:55,937 --> 01:22:57,336
Attention, everyone!

986
01:22:57,572 --> 01:23:00,962
I have an announcement to make.
Surprise! Surprise!

987
01:23:01,242 --> 01:23:03,574
Today, after a long
and desperate search...

988
01:23:03,812 --> 01:23:08,806
...I have found a most exciting
entry for the Salzburg Folk Festival.

989
01:23:09,050 --> 01:23:10,847
Congratulations, Max.

990
01:23:11,119 --> 01:23:14,077
And who will you
be exploiting this time?

991
01:23:15,824 --> 01:23:19,089
- The Saint Ignatius Choir?
- Guess again.

992
01:23:19,794 --> 01:23:23,685
Well, let me see now.
The Klopmann Choir?

993
01:23:23,965 --> 01:23:26,297
- No, no, no, no.
- No, no?

994
01:23:26,568 --> 01:23:27,762
Tell us.

995
01:23:27,969 --> 01:23:31,427
A singing group all in one family.
You'll never guess, Georg.

996
01:23:31,673 --> 01:23:34,562
What a charming idea!

997
01:23:34,809 --> 01:23:36,606
Whose family?

998
01:23:37,479 --> 01:23:39,106
Yours.

999
01:23:39,314 --> 01:23:41,612
They'll be the talk of the festival.

1000
01:23:44,486 --> 01:23:47,478
- Well, now, what's so funny?
- You are, Max.

1001
01:23:47,722 --> 01:23:50,850
You're expensive, but very funny.

1002
01:23:51,626 --> 01:23:53,958
- They'll be a sensation!
- No, Max.

1003
01:23:54,195 --> 01:23:56,356
It's a wonderful idea.
Fresh, original.

1004
01:23:56,598 --> 01:24:01,388
Max! My children
do not sing in public.

1005
01:24:02,103 --> 01:24:04,025
You can't blame me for trying.

1006
01:24:04,239 --> 01:24:07,231
Children, who shall we hear
from next?

1007
01:24:10,045 --> 01:24:11,205
Who?

1008
01:24:17,352 --> 01:24:18,614
Yes.

1009
01:24:21,489 --> 01:24:23,377
The vote is unanimous.

1010
01:24:24,225 --> 01:24:25,817
You, captain.

1011
01:24:26,061 --> 01:24:27,255
Me?

1012
01:24:28,129 --> 01:24:30,393
- I don't understand.
- Please.

1013
01:24:36,638 --> 01:24:38,731
No, no, no, no.

1014
01:24:39,007 --> 01:24:41,032
I'm told that you were quite good.

1015
01:24:41,242 --> 01:24:44,575
- That was a very, very long time ago.
- I remember, Father.

1016
01:24:44,846 --> 01:24:47,701
- Play us something we know.
- Oh, please, Father.

1017
01:24:50,585 --> 01:24:51,677
Well...

1018
01:25:01,963 --> 01:25:04,124
- Why didn't you tell me?
- What?

1019
01:25:04,399 --> 01:25:06,731
To bring along my harmonica.

